              <p data-hf-id="hf-nbhw" style="margin-top:6px"><b data-hf-id="hf-tw68">How to use the calculator:</b> Use the <span data-hf-id="hf-emvg" class="lnk">Basic Percentage CALCULATOR</span> ("What is X% of Y?"). Enter the tip percentage as <span data-hf-id="hf-5u3f" id="det-x">10</span> [X] and the bill amount as <span data-hf-id="hf-12ez" id="det-y">150</span> [Y]. It will calculate <span data-hf-id="hf-nw2t" id="det-x2">10</span>% of <span data-hf-id="hf-yvob" id="det-y2">150</span>.</p>
              <p data-hf-id="hf-nmt8" style="margin-top:6px"><b data-hf-id="hf-jeek">The formula:</b> Formula: (Percentage / 100) × Whole. Tip amount = (<span data-hf-id="hf-t991" id="det-fx">10</span> / 100) × <span data-hf-id="hf-kg35" id="det-fy">150</span> = <span data-hf-id="hf-9xjc" id="det-fr">15</span></p>
